{
  "text": "Lentivirus vectors expressing shRNAs have been shown to promote specific gene silencing in primary dendritic cells [CITATION_1] , whilst CD8-specific shRNAs expressed from an HIV-1-based vector have been found capable of silencing CD8 expression in vitro and in vivo [CITATION_2] . Collectively, these studies illustrate the broad utility of RNAi for the silencing of viral and cellular processes in vitro and in vivo.",
  "citation_candidates": [
